<subSubSection id="66F26515BC647054D0C8FAEDFE13DEB2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC647054D0C8FAEDFE13DEB2" blockId="6.[151,1437,1228,1936]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC647054D0C8FAEDFEC3DE5E" bold="true" box="[199,321,1335,1360]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Idiosoma dorsally and ventrally sclerotized except for a narrow strip of papillose integument extending around coxal and genital field, and two median strips extending posteriorly from the posteromedial corner of Cx-IV to about two-third of the postgenital length; gonopore surrounded by a row of small setae and located on a raised high ridge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66F26515BC647054D0C8FA1DFC67DC9E" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC647054D0C8FA1DFC67DC9E" blockId="6.[151,1437,1228,1936]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC647054D0C8FA1DFEDADEEE" bold="true" box="[199,344,1479,1504]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus id="F153883CBC647054D1A1FA12FD96DEEE" box="[430,532,1480,1504]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
, in parentheses measurements of 
<typeStatus id="F153883CBC647054D393FA13FC7EDEEF" box="[924,1020,1481,1505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">paratype</typeStatus>
specimens) — Idiosoma L/W 1280 (1040 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC647054D0D7FA36FF64DD0A" bold="true" box="[216,230,1516,1540]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
1410) /1100 (950 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC647054D1A5FA36FE3ADD0A" bold="true" box="[426,440,1516,1540]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
1250); idiosoma dorsally and ventrally sclerotized except for a narrow strip of papillose integument extending around coxal and genital field, and two median strips extending posteriorly from the posteromedial corner of Cx-IV to about two-third of the postgenital length (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC647054D3B5F9EEFB83DD42" box="[954,1025,1588,1612]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1659,1682]" captionTargetBox="[193,1418,196,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-158@8.[151,1436,163,1638]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hydrachna sistanica sp. nov., holotype male: idiosoma, ventral view. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); coxal field: L 581, W 925; Cx-IV bearing one seta, posteromedial corner extending, with a cleaver-shaped extension of secondary sclerotization. Genital field L/W 252/216, heart-shaped, posteriorly extending beyond posterior margin of Cx-IV, anteriorly with a small indentation, gonopore surrounded by a row of small setae and located on a raised high ridge as shown in 
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC647054D56AF97AFF5EDDD2" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@9.[151,1436,193,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–F. Hydrachna sistanica sp. nov., holotype male: A = genital field, with medial margin of Cx-III+IV; B = genital field; C = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp; F = I–L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs. 5A 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC647054D0B6F91EFF45DDD2" bold="true" box="[185,199,1732,1756]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
B
</figureCitation>
; genital field hinged at anterior end but movable posteriorly, this movement leads to apparent differences in placement of the gonopore (see 
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC647054D1F1F932FD03DC0E" box="[510,641,1768,1792]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@9.[151,1436,193,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–F. Hydrachna sistanica sp. nov., holotype male: A = genital field, with medial margin of Cx-III+IV; B = genital field; C = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp; F = I–L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs. 5A 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC647054D251F932FDEEDC0E" bold="true" box="[606,620,1768,1792]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
B
</figureCitation>
); Ac small, but one larger Ac on each side located in the posterolateral part of the acetabular field. Gnathosoma stout, L 491, rostrum L 228, shorter than base, bent ventrally with a distinct kink (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC647054D11FF8EAFEE5DC46" box="[272,359,1840,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@9.[151,1436,193,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–F. Hydrachna sistanica sp. nov., holotype male: A = genital field, with medial margin of Cx-III+IV; B = genital field; C = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp; F = I–L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); chelicera L 572; palp (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC647054D277F8EAFD7FDC46" box="[632,765,1840,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@9.[151,1436,193,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–F. Hydrachna sistanica sp. nov., holotype male: A = genital field, with medial margin of Cx-III+IV; B = genital field; C = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp; F = I–L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs. 5D 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC647054D2D5F8EAFD6ADC46" bold="true" box="[730,744,1840,1864]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">–</emphasis>
E
</figureCitation>
): total L 584; dL: P-1, 166; P-2, 138; P-3, 163; P-4, 81; P-5, 36; P-1 bearing one dorsodistal seta, P-2 strongly convex dorsally, ventral margin concave. Legs: dL of I-L-2-6 (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC647054D090F8A2FF77DC9E" box="[159,245,1912,1936]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@9.[151,1436,193,1868]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–F. Hydrachna sistanica sp. nov., holotype male: A = genital field, with medial margin of Cx-III+IV; B = genital field; C = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp; F = I–L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
): 144, 98, 113, 141, 168; dL of IV-L: 193, 175, 140, 244, 263, 242.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
