</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype male: idiosoma, ventral view. Scale bar = 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="66F26515BC6A705AD0C8F963FB18DDDE" box="[199,1178,1720,1745]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC6A705AD0C8F963FB18DDDE" blockId="8.[151,1436,1720,1997]" box="[199,1178,1720,1745]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD0C8F963FECFDDDF" bold="true" box="[199,333,1721,1745]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named for its occurrence in 
<collectingRegion id="EC2CF87CBC6A705AD33DF962FB14DDDE" box="[818,1174,1720,1744]" country="Iran" name="Sistan va Baluchestan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Sistan va Baluchestan Province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66F26515BC6A705AD0C8F907FDCDDCA6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC6A705AD0C8F907FA08DC8B" blockId="8.[151,1436,1720,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD0C8F907FEB9DDFB" bold="true" box="[199,315,1757,1781]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Due to the characteristic shape of the genital field, with its raised ridge surrounding the gonopore, and an extensive dorsal sclerotization, 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC6A705AD249F8DBFCACDC16" authority="Pešić &amp; Smit &amp; Saboori, 2012" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit &amp; Saboori" authorityYear="2012" box="[582,814,1793,1817]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sistanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD249F8DBFCACDC16" box="[582,814,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hydrachna sistanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD33AF8DBFC0CDC17" bold="true" box="[821,910,1793,1817]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="07AF57F7BC6A705AD33AF8DBFC0CDC17" box="[821,910,1793,1817]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC6A705AD453F8DBFA06DC16" authority="Cook, 1967" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[1116,1412,1792,1816]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysorensis">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD453F8DBFB7BDC16" box="[1116,1273,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. mysorensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4A794B6FBC6A705AD50FF8DAFA06DC16" author="Cook, D. R." box="[1280,1412,1792,1816]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref32903" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species described from a pond in Mysore State in 
<collectingCountry id="56FF760EBC6A705AD2C2F8FFFC84DC33" box="[717,774,1829,1853]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4A794B6FBC6A705AD319F8FFFC1ADC33" author="Cook, D. R." box="[790,920,1829,1853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref32903" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook 1967</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC6A705AD3A3F8FFFB2CDC33" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[940,1198,1829,1853]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysorensis">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD3A3F8FFFB2CDC33" box="[940,1198,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hydrachna mysorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the new species by the lack of ventral secondary sclerotization (see 
<bibRefCitation id="4A794B6FBC6A705AD3EDF892FBE0DC6E" author="Cook, D. R." box="[994,1122,1864,1888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref32903" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC6A705AD47FF892FB47DC6E" box="[1136,1221,1864,1888]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[178,1389,188,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-75@36.[170,1418,171,1932]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 25A–F. Atractides hormozganus sp. nov., male (B–C, E — holotype, A, F — paratype from IR21-2011, D — specimen from IR18-2011): A = idiosoma, ventral view; B = ejaculatory complex; C–D = genital field; E = palp, lateral view; F = palp, medial view. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, our species does not show the extreme humped condition of the dorsal side of P-2 which is typical for 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD4EAF8B4FA08DC8B" box="[1253,1418,1902,1925]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC6A705AD4EAF8B4FA05DC8B" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[1253,1415,1902,1925]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysorensis">H. mysorensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC6A705AD0C8F84AFDCDDCA6" blockId="8.[151,1436,1720,1997]" box="[199,591,1936,1961]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC6A705AD0C8F84AFEA8DCA7" bold="true" box="[199,298,1936,1961]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Standing water (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC6A705AD1E7F84AFDC0DCA6" box="[488,578,1936,1960]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,249,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-79@13.[188,1398,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8A–B. Standing water habitats: A — pool in Gerdoig village (collecting site of Hydrachna cf. vaillanti, H. globosa lacerata, Diplodontus silvestrii and Limnesia pinguipalpis, and locus typicus of Hydrachna sistanica); B — pool in saline stream near Khorgoo village (collecting site of Haloaxonopsis salina and locus typicus of Limnesia diversipes). Photos. V. Pešić." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
